# Project Setup Walkthrough - Paperclip

I have successfully set up the Paperclip project for you.

## Accomplishments
- **Cloned Repository**: Cloned the Paperclip repository into `c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\paperclip2`.
- **Installed Dependencies**: Ran `pnpm install` across all packages in the workspace.
- **Created Startup Script**: Created `start_paperclip.bat` to automate the startup process.
- **Verified Codebase**: Ran `pnpm -r typecheck` to ensure there are no compilation errors.

## Verification Results
- **Typecheck**: All packages passed type checking.
- **Startup Script**: Verified the existence and content of [start_paperclip.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip2/start_paperclip.bat).

## Next Steps
1.  Run the [start_paperclip.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip2/start_paperclip.bat) file to start the services.
2.  Open your browser and navigate to `http://localhost:3100` to interact with the UI.
3.  The API health check will be available at `http://localhost:3100/api/health`.

> [!NOTE]
> The project is configured to use an embedded PGlite database by default, so no external database setup is required for initial development.
